17/11/2008
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- The Kosovo Police Service's anti-terrorism and serious-crime units are investigating the attack on the offices of the International Civilian Office on Friday evening (November 14th), but there is no word on possible suspects.
According to media reports Monday, attackers threw 100 to 200g of TNT from a moving vehicle.
Leaders condemned the incident immediately.
"This terrible act aims at damaging the partnership of Kosovo with the international community," Parliament Speaker Jakup Krasniqi said.
(Koha Ditore, Zeri, Lajm, Express - 17/11/08)
